<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,789]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,620,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Yang" authorityName="Yang" authorityYear="1995" box="[654,861,620,645]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ampliatus">
<emphasis box="[654,796,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">A. ampliatus</emphasis>
Yang
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[930,988,620,645]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Tibet</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1003,1076,620,645]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">China</collectingCountry>
), but may be separated from the latter by the size of cercus and the shape of the surstylus. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yang" authorityYear="1995" box="[826,967,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ampliatus">
<emphasis box="[826,967,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">A. ampliatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the cercus is small, less than half as long as the epandrium; the surstylus has an independent sclerite basally (
<bibRefCitation author="Yang, D." box="[907,1033,692,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="179 - 181" refId="ref25359" refString="Yang, D. (1995) Three new species of the subfamily Sciapodinae from China (Diptera, Dolichopodidae). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique Entomologie, 65, 179 - 181." type="journal article" year="1995">Yang 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yang, D. &amp; Zhang, L. &amp; Wang, M. &amp; Zhu, Y." box="[1045,1229,692,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="111 - 291" refId="ref25610" refString="Yang, D., Zhang, L., Wang, M. &amp; Zhu, Y. (2011) Fauna Sinica Insecta Uol. 53. Diptera Dolichopodidae. Science Press, Beijing, pp. 111 - 291." type="book chapter" year="2011">
Yang 
<emphasis box="[1109,1165,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 50). The 
<typeStatus box="[1387,1436,693,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">type</typeStatus>
specimens were collected in bushes alongside open water.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
